Alec B. Francis https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alec_B._Francis 0 Alec B. Francis (born Alec Francis Budd, 2 December 1867 – 6 July 1934) was an English actor, largely of the silent era. He appeared in 241 films between 1911 and 1934. He was born in London and died in Hollywood, California.
